subject: Re: Collecting proposals for 4.12 features and bugs
msgSnippet: Hi David, I failed to apply the label myself, but I d like to nominate https://github.com/KentBeck/junit/pull/529 Cheers, Stephan
messageBody:
Hi David,

I failed to apply the label myself, but I'd like to nominate https://github.com/KentBeck/junit/pull/529

Cheers,
Stephan

--- In junit@yahoogroups.com, David Saff <saff@...> wrote:
>
> All,
>
> As 4.11 nears release, I've started a github label to track features and
> bugs that are of small- to medium-scope, and clear benefit. Feel free to
> nominate one or two of your favorites:
>
> https://github.com/KentBeck/junit/issues?direction=asc&labels=targeted-to-4.12&page=1&sort=updated&state=open
>
> If you move something into the list, please also comment on the issue,
> because I don't think that it generates a notification otherwise.
>
> No promises, of course, but I think this may provide a way to filter to the
> top those issues that are hold the most potential. Thanks,
>
> David Saff
>
>
> [Non-text portions of this message have been removed]
>
